headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 29 points, 14 rebounds and six assists and the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a three-game losing streak with a 144-114 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid, Harris help lead 76ers to 144-114 rout of Hornets

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 24 points and 13 assists to lead the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 119-101 win over the New York Knicks on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers cruise to 119-101 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant earned a new scoring record, though it was Danilo Gallinari and the Atlanta Hawks who celebrated with a postgame toast.
headlines.shortLinkText: Streaking Hawks survive Durant's 55, hold off Nets 122-115

headlines.description: — The Miami Heat appear to be back on steady ground after stumbling through a season-high four straight losses. Their grip on the No. 1 seed in the Eastern Conference is tightening, too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 22, Heat beat Bulls 127-109 for 50th win

events.name: Utah Jazz at Golden State Warriors
